---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Introduction" currentSlug="">
  <h1>CommandCenter Docs</h1>
  <p>
    CommandCenter is a terminal-of-terminals and agent orchestrator: one
    window that hosts many projects, each with its own processes,
    terminals, and AI agents. These pages are a starter for real
    documentation as the app gets built out.
  </p>

  <h2>Current status</h2>
  <p>
    This is an early skeleton. <code>list_projects</code> and
    <code>list_processes</code> return placeholder data; there is no real
    process engine wired up yet. The app shell (sidebar, search modal,
    theming) is functional; the underlying orchestration is not.
  </p>

  <h2>Where to go next</h2>
  <div class="docs-blocks">
    <a class="docs-block" href="/docs/ai/agents">
      <span class="docs-block__label">AI Fundamentals</span>
      <span class="docs-block__title">What is an AI coding agent</span>
      <span class="docs-block__desc">
        The agent loop, prompting basics, and how MCP tools fit in --
        general concepts, not CommandCenter-specific.
      </span>
    </a>
    <a class="docs-block" href="/docs/projects">
      <span class="docs-block__label">About CommandCenter</span>
      <span class="docs-block__title">Projects, processes, and agents</span>
      <span class="docs-block__desc">
        How this application is actually put together: the credential
        store, the MCP server, the app shell, and what's still a stub.
      </span>
    </a>
  </div>

  <style>
    .docs-blocks {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 12px;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }

    .docs-block {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 4px;
      padding: 16px;
      border: 1px solid var(--cc-border);
      border-radius: 10px;
      text-decoration: none;
      transition: background 0.15s ease, border-color 0.15s ease;
    }

    .docs-block:hover {
      background: var(--cc-hover-bg);
      border-color: var(--cc-border-strong);
    }

    .docs-block__label {
      font-size: 0.7em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      color: var(--cc-accent);
    }

    .docs-block__title {
      font-size: 1.05em;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--cc-text);
    }

    .docs-block__desc {
      font-size: 0.85em;
      line-height: 1.5;
      color: var(--cc-text-muted);
    }

    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      .docs-blocks {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>
</DocsLayout>
